<section id="explanation-3" class="level3">
<h3 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="explanation-3"><strong>Explanation:</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Standard <code>for()</code> loops</strong> execute sequentially, which is slow for large-scale tasks.</li>
<li><strong><code>foreach()</code> with <code>doParallel</code></strong> allows parallel execution, <strong>leveraging multiple CPU cores</strong>.</li>
<li><code>makeCluster(parallel::detectCores() - 1)</code> ensures all but one core are used, <strong>preventing system overload</strong>.</li>
</ul>
